    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds a bit too \"seamless\" for comfort tbh. if they can do that with lights and thermostats, it means they're basically running a constant emotional analysis on me in my own house. do you think a company would actually test these kinds of surveillance algorithms on regular people without telling them? like, using us as guinea pigs for their emotional tracking tech?",
